Goanad <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub41.ezboard.com/ubakxs.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Bakxs</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Contributing Member</span><br>  Posts: 414<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(4/10/02 5:36:48 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub41.ezboard.com/fvazaellecommunitycenterfrm5.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1084.topic&index=47>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> AE Group Theory</span><hr size=1> AE groups are incredible experience generating machines.  But how do they work?<br>
<br>
Pretty simple, actually...  <br>
<br>
You need a group--5 to 6 people who all know their roles.  The only essential class it the enchanter...  the other roles can be filled by a variety of other classes.  <br>
<br>
The other two roles besides the enchanter is healer and damage dealer.  <br>
<br>
The process goes as follows:<br>
--Someone or a couple of peeps go out and pull mobs.  As many as they can get without getting killed in the process<br>
--They bring all those mobs back to camp.  <br>
--The enchanters chain AE stun.  This prevents the mobs from attacking<br>
--The cleric or healer there heals those who are getting hurt.  Keep the enchanter alive at all costs.  <br>
--The pullers go out and get more mobs.<br>
--The enchanters continue the stunning.  <br>
--When the mobs are in camp and everyone is back, everyone who has AE damage start unleashing.  <br>
--ML goes and loots all the goodies.  <br>
<br>
Pretty simple, huh?  Killing 40, 50 or even more mobs are possible for every &quot;pull&quot;.  Phat xp.  <br>
<br>
Be sure to keep enchanter alive.  If your enchanter(s) die, the game is pretty much over.  Mages are nice to have as ModRod2 really cuts down on downtime.  Wizards with epics make really good pullers.  <br>
<br>
There may be other stuff I'm missing...  but that pretty much gives you a good idea of what's going on.  <br>
<br>
Enjoy!<br>
<br>
--B<br>
<br>
